title: Printer's Sample Book, 1866–75
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used on printed textiles. Contains 72 fabric samples in a variety of patterns.

tombstone.epitaph:
Printer's Sample Book, 1866–75.
1866–75. Medium: paper and cotton. Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts. 1945-55-34.
